                "name": "Freedom",
                "ability_type": "Spell-Like",
                "ability_type_abbrev": "Sp",
                "text": "Whenever a cerynitis is affected by a spell or effect that would be removed by <i>freedom</i>, she is instantly affected by <i>freedom</i>."
            },
            {
                "type": "stat_block_section",
                "subtype": "special_ability",
                "name": "Sacred Grace",
                "ability_type": "Extraordinary",
                "ability_type_abbrev": "Ex",
                "text": "A cerynitis is blessed by her patron deity, allowing her to always act on the surprise round and granting her a sacred bonus to AC and initiative equal to her Charisma bonus."
            },
            {
                "type": "stat_block_section",
                "subtype": "special_ability",
                "name": "Uncanny Dodge",
                "ability_type": "Extraordinary",
                "ability_type_abbrev": "Ex",
                "text": "This ability functions as the rogue class feature of the same name."
            },
            {
                "type": "stat_block_section",
                "subtype": "special_ability",
                "name": "Unearthly Speed",
                "ability_type": "Extraordinary",
                "ability_type_abbrev": "Ex",
                "text": "When a creature makes a ranged or melee attack against a cerynitis, targets her with an ability, or includes her in the area of effect of an ability, the cerynitis can move up to half her speed as if she had readied an action to move. If she moves at all, this foils ranged and melee attacks; if she moves out of the area of effect, she avoids an area of effect ability; if she moves out of range of the targeted effect, she avoids a targeted ability. Once she uses this ability, a cerynitis can\u2019t use it again for 1 round. Each use of this ability counts as a move action for the purpose of triggering Lightning Stance. A cerynitis can\u2019t use unearthly speed to avoid an attack or ability if she is not aware of the attack or ability, and she cannot use this ability at all if she is rendered immobile or if she bears a rider."
            }
        ]
